To kill some user's ssh session 
kill its ssh session. Check them by

	ps aux | egrep "sshd: [a-zA-Z]+@"
Second column gives you the PID. Then,

	sudo kill -9 [PID]

	sudo ufw allow 80/tcp
	sudo ufw show added
	sudo ufw enable

Mounting a partition as read only in ubuntu
	udisksctl mount --block-device /dev/sda3 --options ro

Mounting external hard disk if faced an error MTFMirr doesnot match

	sudo ntfsfix /dev/sdb1

To show files sorted by modifying time
ls -t